28	 *
29	 * <ol>
30	 *   <li>The session must not be cancelled.</li>
31	 *   <li>Capacity must not be exceeded.</li>
32	 *   <li>The student must not already have a non-terminal booking that overlaps
33	 *       the target session's time window (prevents double-booking across
34	 *       concurrent classes).</li>
35	 * </ol>
36	 *
37	 * <p>Phase B6 lifecycle: bookings start in {@link Booking.Status#INITIATED}
38	 * when first created. A reviewer (or the self-service flow) transitions them
39	 * through {@link #confirm(Long, String) confirm},
40	 * {@link #cancel(Long, String) cancel}, and
41	 * {@link #refund(Long, int, String, String) refund}. Legal transitions:
42	 *
43	 * <pre>
44	 *   INITIATED → CONFIRMED
45	 *   INITIATED → CANCELED
46	 *   CONFIRMED → CANCELED
47	 *   CANCELED  → REFUNDED   (posts credit-ledger entry)
48	 * </pre>
49	 *
50	 * Refunds are never cash — only internal credit. The refund call creates a
51	 * {@link CreditTransaction} via {@link CreditService#adjust} and stores the
52	 * resulting tx id on the booking. Scope enforcement delegates to the
53	 * session's parent organization.
